Shocking video shows women launching themselves at a moving train during rush hour in MumbaiThe video shows the moment one woman hoists herself up into the open door before the train stops, while numerous others immediately launch themselves at the entrance.Passengers even fall down the gap between the train and the platform in the rush and are almost crushed by the carriage and the other women trying to board.According to Daily Mail, in India, women-only trains were introduced in Delhi, Mumbai, Calcutta and Madras in 2009 in order to provide safety for female travellers. The competition to get a seat on the trains during rush hour has caused several accidents, with many even losing their lives trying to board the carriages. 